"{\"uid\": \"toronto.citynews.ca-2024-06-18-paris-gets-into-the-groove-for-historic-olympic-opening-ceremony-adapted-to-its-iconic-cityscape\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Adjust preferences  With your consent we may collect cookies and information to enhance our service, and improve your experience.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 129, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These cookies and data are essential for browsing our website and allowing services.\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Examples include, session, authentication, and security cookies.\", \"from\": 216, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These cookies and data enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalized content.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These cookies and data inform us which pages are most informative and engaging via analytics.\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These cookies may track data across websites for marketing and interest-based advertising to provide personalized content, offers, and advertisements.\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Toronto  By Thomas Adamson And John Leicester, The Associated Press  Posted June 18, 2024 5:01 am.\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1081238631114401e-23, \"text\": \"Toronto\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\"}, {\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Adamson_(soldier)\", \"score\": 0.9999315390348512, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Adamson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Adamson_(soldier)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Adamson_(soldier)\"}, {\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leicester\", \"score\": 0.9999999961783033, \"rank\": 3.744119007095538e-09, \"text\": \"Leicester\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leicester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leicester\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last Updated June 18, 2024 5:12 am.\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SAINT-DENIS, France (AP) - TheParis Olympicsare getting into the groove for the historic opening ceremony on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 769, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9902937334800022, \"rank\": 0.009801060545812347, \"text\": \"SAINT-DENIS\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999979391889927, \"rank\": 1.9154681783678475e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 790, \"end\": 792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3219698923830227e-13, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dancers who will jazz upthe July 26 showunder the artistic direction of prize-winning French theater directorThomas Jollyare putting finishing touches on a high-octane performance that will combine urban, contemporary, classic, and break dancing, complete with stomps, shouts, and body rolls.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 982, \"end\": 996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theatre_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.923210660155397e-17, \"text\": \"French theater\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theatre_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theatre_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press got a behind-the-scenes look of one of their rehearsals, providing an advance peek into preparations for the opening show that is largely shrouded in secrecy.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1194, \"end\": 1210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999438564627311, \"rank\": 5.6146689508970936e-05, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dance director Maud Le Pladec instructed around 50 dancers on their twists and turns at a warehouse in the northern Parisian suburb of Saint-Denis.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She spoke with pride of the rich cultural mix of her melting-pot troupe, declaring: \\\"It represents the part of France I love.\\\"\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1629, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999979391889927, \"rank\": 1.9154681783678475e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are in France but we are talking to the whole world,\\\" she said, \\\"which means we have different identities, bodies, ages.\\\"\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999979391889927, \"rank\": 1.9154681783678475e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The grandiose open-air ceremony will beheld during sunsetand is expected to last nearly four hours, transforming the heart of Paris and its iconic landmarks into a giant stage for Jolly's artistic talents but also requiring a massive security effort.\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8510267320852327e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"An opening ceremony has never been held outside of a stadium.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2087, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no model, it's absolute creation,\\\" Jolly said in an interview published Tuesday by Le Parisien newspaper.\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2180, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Parisien\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Detailing how he's had to revisit some of his ideas to fit the urban environment, Jolly said he'd imagined having a giant ballet with 200 dancers on one of the bridges that span the Seine but, after a study was done, \\\"we were told that everyone doing the same step at the same time would endanger the bridge's solidity.\\\"\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2524, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2386, \"end\": 2391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2344745865403984e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also said: \\\"I wanted to build an upside-down Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought it would be pretty for lighting the Olympic flame.\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2648, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it wasn't doable.\\\"\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The initial overall concept for the ceremony has had to be adapted \\\"so that the dream and the reality meet,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 2673, \"to\": 2791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For security services,the unprecedented decisionto parade thousands of Olympians on boats along a 6-kilometer (3.7-mile) stretch ofthe Seine, from Pont d'Austerlitz to Pont d'I\\u00e9na, in front of a 320,000-strong crowd is a huge challenge.\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 3029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2928, \"end\": 2933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2344745865403984e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2940, \"end\": 2957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont d'Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 2961, \"end\": 2972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'I\\u00e9na\", \"score\": 0.999999712782524, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont d'I\\u00e9na\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'I\\u00e9na\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'I\\u00e9na\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About 45,000 security force members will be deployed and the airspace and all airports within a 150-kilometer (90-mile) radius around Paris will be closed for the extravaganza.\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3164, \"end\": 3169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8510267320852327e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tickets will be free for about220,000 invited and security-screened spectatorswatching from upper tiers of the river's banks.\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"About 100,000 paying spectators, including lavish hospitality packages, will watch from the lower riverside and around the Trocad\\u00e9ro plaza - where the parade will end looking across to the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3536, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"score\": 0.9730907954876998, \"rank\": 0.023351147168026228, \"text\": \"Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers hope the show will leave an indelible imprint on the massive global television audience and demonstrate French can-do and say it will aim to showcase France's heritage, history and creativity.\", \"from\": 3538, \"to\": 3741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3699, \"end\": 3705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999979391889927, \"rank\": 1.9154681783678475e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was, of course, a very audacious decision not to go into a stadium but into the city.\", \"from\": 3743, \"to\": 3832, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will mark the history of our country for quite a long time,\\\" said Tony Estanguet, head of the Paris Games organizing committee, who attended the dance rehearsal.\", \"from\": 3833, \"to\": 3997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3902, \"end\": 3916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers say a total of 3,000 dancers will feature in the opening and closing ceremonies for the July 26-Aug. 11 Olympics andthe Paralympicsthat follow from Aug. 28 to Sept. 8.\", \"from\": 3999, \"to\": 4177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dancer Sharlyne Say, 22, described the prospect of performing on a global stage as a \\\"dream come true.\\\"\", \"from\": 4179, \"to\": 4282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4195, \"end\": 4198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Say\", \"score\": 0.9999999993842721, \"rank\": 6.156214597186874e-10, \"text\": \"Say\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q188094\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Say\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Say\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It will be crazy,\\\" she added, \\\"because I am not used to dancing outside.\\\"\", \"from\": 4284, \"to\": 4358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"___  Leicester reported from Paris.\", \"from\": 4360, \"to\": 4395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4389, \"end\": 4394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8510267320852327e-28, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \